This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with instance segmentation, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. The paper also proposes a novel approach for learning instance segmentation, which involves the use of attention maps and inter-pixel relations. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper proposes a neural network architecture (IRNet) for generating pseudo labels, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
